schema-org:description.@value: This is an alternate identifier for the PurchaseOrder, requires the use of the typeCode qualifier.  This could be a system level key.
additional textual reason for the reason the status code has been applied or the if the effective time period has changed.
This is the customer representative placing the order, including name, phone and email contact information
Directions for the location, especially in the case of direct ship
URI link to a mapping service showing the exact location on a map
This is the key contact at the ShipTo location, in case there are delivery questions.
delivery point may be a loading dock, etc.
Two character state code in the United States, Province in Canada, etc.  See ISO 3166-2.
This is the physical address for the shipment
This is the total amount of the purchase order, which is the sum of each purchase order lines, plus calculated tax.
Identifier for the BillTo party
Specific Account for the customer BillTo
Identifier for the location, if no GLN is used.
Two character state code in the United States, Province in Canada, etc.  See ISO 3166-2.
This is the mailing address for which invoices should be sent, if not electronically sent.

Note on the BillTo lcoation
Example:
This is the BillTo contact
customer's account number with the carrier if the customer is specifying a carrier
state or province from which the tax applies.
sum of the individual items without tax
current exchange rate at the time of the transaciton
These are various taxes that may be applied.  There may be multiple tax values for VAT, etc.
Identifier for the buyer

This is often not known at the time the order is place, but will appear on the AcknowledgePurchaseOrder Callback API or 
GET //AcknowledgePurchaseOrder request response service

Code used to classify the item being purchased.
If code is mapped, the typeCode should also be mapped since this a generic code.
If the ShipTo defines an import of the product into the country, the identifiers for customs clearance are required.
Calculated amount based on percentage.
If provided, customer service will evaluate for applicability.
